  "title": "Planner (Manufacturing/Production, East Region)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities: </strong></p><ul><li>Develop and optimize shop floor scheduling to achieve throughput targets.</li><li>Set monthly WIP and production targets to meet global inventory DOH requirements.</li><li>Evaluate equipment capacity through time studies and material flow analysis.</li><li>Drive continuous improvements in capacity utilization and material flow.</li><li>Manage yield and process time variation to ensure customer demand fulfilment.</li><li>Plan ingot growing based on product mix and puller capacity.</li><li>Coordinate ingot deliveries to overseas manufacturing sites.</li><li>Adjust production starts and ingot growing plans to support changes in product specifications.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements: </strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Engineering or equivalent.</li><li>Knowledge of logistics processes and systems in manufacturing.</li><li>Understanding of manufacturing processes and product costing.</li><li>Strong PC and Microsoft Excel skills (Visual Basic a plus).</li><li>Basic knowledge of C++.</li></ul><p><strong>______________________________________________________</strong></p><p><strong>HOW TO APPLY :</strong></p><p><strong>Interested candidates, please submit your resume by clicking on “Quick Apply” or contact win@hkmsvs.com for more details.</strong></p><p><strong>Please provide following information in the resume for immediate processing</strong></p><p><strong>1) Reasons for leaving current and/or last employment</strong></p><p><strong>2) Last drawn and/or current salary</strong></p><p><strong>3) Expected salary</strong></p><p><strong>4) Date of availability and/or Notice Period</strong></p><p><strong>All applications will be treated in strictest confidence and only shortlisted candidates will be notified</strong></p><p><strong>Wee Wai Dan</strong></p><p><strong>EA License No : 03C5391</strong></p><p><strong>EA Reg No : R22109628</strong></p>",
